        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 6:14PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 614 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Virginia Commonwealth University, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, heavy rain, and frequent
lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Reduced visibility and minor flooding
possible. Frequent cloud to ground lightning strikes.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Richmond, Highland Springs, and East Highland Park around 620 PM
EDT.
Bottoms Bridge around 650 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Richmond
International, Wrights Corner, Quinton, Fair Oaks, Richmond Heights,
Varina, Orapax Farms, Elko, Montrose, and Sandston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
